It's February 23rd, I'm doing a trade show in town, and I didn't want to miss American Idol tonight, as they are cutting them down to the top 24... and I'm an Idol-head.
So the plan, with about an hour and some minutes to Idol, was to go to Metro, eat there, and leave with "togo" containers when it was fifteen minutes to Idol.
We're staying at the Hilton Grand Vacation on Karen.
Oh, and my 4 star rating?
Consider it more a 3.5, but if you average in the decent layout for family and kids, the more complete menu beyond pies, and overall experience, I have to go with 4 stars.
So, I'm in Vegas for a trade show, again.
And when here, like any local, I do have my favorite "off strip" hotels, and my favorite restaurants.
For a few years I preferred to stay at the Hawthorn Suites hotel apartments at Joe E. Brown off Tropicana.
And during that time, did my grocery shopping and pizza ordering all along Tropicana going East off the strip.
That's when I discovered Metro on Tropicana.
I've done this location before with my family, when they were in town, and by myself.
So having come here more than once, I had to agree with Jacob M's review, I find them to be inconsistent in their pies and service.
The pies go from OK, to good, to very good, and the service can sometimes be "rushed"..... as in, you may feel you're getting the "bum's rush.
" They do get busy, and your table may be visited by bus boys refilling your drinks, in lieu of your server.
But to focus on the pizza, it is good, but I won't say great.
We actually ordered two individual pies and an appetizer of wings.
And we did "pack it up" when I saw we were fifteen minutes from Idol.
The plan did work.
If in Vegas, and you're willing to veer off the strip for awhile, this is your better alternative to any chain pizza.
Plus, they do the Italian pizza deli menu with calzones, spaghettis, chicken parm and a bit more.
But if in search of the "ultimate" in Vegas "brick oven" style pizza ...
I believe it's out there, but I haven't found or done it yet.
That's the next search on my list.

