I have been a fan of Metro Pizza since I was in high school.
I'm  now 26.
So, take that into account and note my loyalty to this specific pizza chain in Las Vegas.
It's good, thin crust pizza made correctly and just the way I like my pizza.
Although my family tends to order this pizza from Boulder Station and have it delivered to our house, I wanted to review the location on Tropicana because I recently went there with my EX for dinner.
First off the place has a nice ambiance, and it BIG, and you don't feel cramped while you're having your pizza.
I find that a lot of pizza joints tend to be small, loud, and often full of children running about.
I realize pizza is an obvious go-to for families, but sometimes you just don't want to deal with that.
Anyway, there were still a lot of families around us, but it wasn't irritating since they were plenty far away.
As for the service: we were seated right away, didn't wait, and our waitress got our drink orders right off the bat.
I had a glass of wine, EX had a beer.
We ordered a Large for the TWO of us, of course, this was my EX's idea, not mine.
So we had PLENTY to take home, in fact - half a pizza.
We ordered off-menu, meaning we just made up what we wanted on the pizza: pepperoni, sausage, and jalapenos.
My only complaint: our waitress took a long time to come around and give us our check.
It was very apparent we were both done eating as we had put our napkins on our plates and had pushed them away.
I even gave her "the look" or tried to at least, a couple times.
We were on a schedule because we were going to catch a movie after dinner.
Anyway, I think she might have assumed we were having a long dinner since we probably looked like we were on a date.
So, no hard feelings for that.
Like I said, I am an avid fan of Metro Pizza and I recommended it to everyone I know!

